---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import NameGenerator from '../components/NameGenerator.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Fantasy Name Generator - Magical & Mythic Names"
  description="Generate thousands of free, magical fantasy names for elves, wizards, dwarves, and adventurers. Customize by gender and count, copy to clipboard, and save your favorites."
  keywords="fantasy name generator, character name generator, elf names, wizard names, dnd names, dwarf names, rpg names"
>
  <div class="space-y-8 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <!-- Header/Intro -->
    <div class="text-center space-y-3">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-[#111111] dark:text-white leading-none">
        Fantasy Name Generator
      </h1>
      <p class="text-base text-[#666666] dark:text-[#888888] max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Create epic, magical, and mythical names for your stories, games, or RPG characters. Our generator compiles names inspired by classic fantasy lore and mythology.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Generator Component -->
    <NameGenerator category="fantasy" categoryName="Fantasy" />

    <!-- SEO Content Section -->
    <section class="border-t border-[#e5e7eb] dark:border-[#222222] pt-10 mt-12 space-y-6 text-[#666666] dark:text-[#888888] text-sm leading-relaxed theme-transition">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-[#111111] dark:text-white">How to Choose the Perfect Fantasy Name</h2>
      <p>
        Finding a name that resonates with your character's backstory, race, and role can be challenging. Whether you are writing a high fantasy novel, preparing for a Dungeons & Dragons campaign, or designing a video game character, follow these tips:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
        <li><strong>Consider Heritage:</strong> Elvish names tend to sound melodic and flowing (like <em>Arwen</em> or <em>Legolas</em>), whereas Dwarven names are often harsh and consonant-heavy (like <em>Gimli</em> or <em>Thorin</em>).</li>
        <li><strong>Match the Tone:</strong> A dark lord needs a powerful, imposing name (like <em>Sauron</em>), while a lighthearted hobbit benefits from friendly, warm names (like <em>Samwise</em>).</li>
        <li><strong>Pronunciation:</strong> Ensure the name is easy to pronounce in speech or read on a page so that players or readers aren't distracted.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
